{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"724e8709-9ae5-4571-9a8b-54761708624e","content":"The problem is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed first. Let me fix this.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_tN85XBjZaxqZSmYB5Lf87e","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-7543f473a8cd4395bacff22a1c66017b/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-7543f473a8cd4395bacff22a1c66017b/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"8476bf2e-b600-4735-9000-9ccbaf0717e6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed before them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. The correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n\n\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":383,"requestId":"0409:37135:46B02D:524629:69F004A9"},"id":"6567263d-d243-4178-8f1c-b50cd40e939f","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:52:00.414Z","parentId":"456751fb-3195-41b6-8117-956d2b42a3d9"}
